Chelsea winger, Willian, has admitted he could play for another Premier League club. Willian has expressed his desire to remain in the Premier League, as his current deal with the Blues enters its final months. The Brazilian joined from Shakhtar Donetsk in 2013 and has made over 300 appearances for the Blues, winning two Premier League titles, the Europa League and FA Cup. With his contract set to expire in June, Willian has been linked with Tottenham and Arsenal. “My desire is to stay in the Premier League, but I don’t rule out playing in other leagues, no,” Willian told ESPN Brazil . “I’m going to play until the end of the season and see what happens. I’m very used to England.”